- On success it returns the location of the mapping
- On error it returns MAP_FAILED and sets errno appropriately ( It never returns zero )
possible errno values
	 EACCESS (not regular file mode of fd conflict with prot and flags)
	EAGAIN - the file has been locked via a fil elcok
	 EBADF - the given fil edescriptor is not valid
	EINVAL- either addr, len or off is invalid
	ENFILE - fopen_max has been reached
	EOVERFLOW - the addr+len exeeds the address space
	EPERM - PROC_EXEC was given but the filesystem in munted noexec
	ENODEV - the file syste

